Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

> If you have a toaster oven, feel free to skip preheating.

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and finely diced). Peel and dice @sweet potatoes{1}(peeled and diced into ½-inch pieces). Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}. Place @butter{2%tbsp} and a pinch of @italian seasoning{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later) in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; bring to room temperature.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add @italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir sweet potato, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, remaining italian seasoning, 2 1/2 cups water (5 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{} into pot. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium and simmer, covered, for ~{7%minutes}.

Once soup has simmered for 7 minutes, uncover pot and stir in kale. Simmer, uncovered, until kale has wilted and sweet potato is tender, ~{5-7%minutes} more. Season generously with salt and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, mix softened butter and italian seasoning until thoroughly combined. Season with salt.

> If butter is not yet softened, microwave for 5-10 seconds.

Halve @demi-baguette{1}; spread herb butter onto cut sides. Toast cut sides up on top rack (or in a #toaster oven{}) until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}. Halve each baguette piece on a diagonal.

Divide soup between #bowls{} and top with @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} if desired. Serve with toasts on the side.